        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 2:48PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 248 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Brownsville-Bawcomville, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Monroe, Claiborne, West Monroe, Brownsville-Bawcom,
Brownsville-Bawcomville, Swartz, Richwood, Drew, Fondale, Millhaven,
Cheniere, Pine Grove, and Lapine.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
